Pentair IntelliCenter for Hubitat
Local WebSocket integration for Pentair IntelliCenter pool controllers. No cloud, no API key — connects directly to your controller on your local network.

Requirements

Pentair IntelliCenter 1 (firmware 1.064 or later) or IntelliCenter 2 (firmware 3.006 or later)
Controller connected to your local network
Hubitat Elevation hub (firmware 2.3.0 or later)
Controller and hub on the same network/subnet


What It Creates
Once connected, the integration automatically discovers and creates devices for:
DeviceDescriptionPool / SpaOn/off switch for each body of waterPool Temp / Spa TempCurrent water temperaturePool Set Point / Spa Set PointTarget temperature with adjustable set pointPool Heater / Spa HeaterHeater on/off and modeCircuitsSwitch for each user circuit (Pool Light, Spa Light, Waterfall, etc.)FeaturesSwitch for each feature relay (Blower, Valves, etc.)VS RPMVariable speed pump RPMVS WattsVariable speed pump wattageAir SensorAir temperatureSolar SensorSolar temperature (if equipped)Salt ChlorinatorChlorinator on/off and salt level

Installation
Option A — Hubitat Package Manager (Recommended)

Open Hubitat Package Manager
Click Install
Search for Pentair IntelliCenter
Select the package and click Next → Install
Follow the setup steps below


Option B — Manual Install
Install in this exact order — all drivers must exist before the app is set up.
Step 1 — Install the Set Point Driver

Go to Drivers Code → New Driver
Paste the contents of intellicenter-setpoint-driver.groovy
Click Save

Step 2 — Install the Bridge Driver

Go to Drivers Code → New Driver
Paste the contents of intellicenter-bridge-driver.groovy
Click Save

Step 3 — Install the App

Go to Apps Code → New App
Paste the contents of intellicenter-app.groovy
Click Save


Setup

Go to Apps → Add User App → Pentair IntelliCenter
Enter your IntelliCenter IP address (e.g. 192.168.1.218)
Leave the port as 6680 (default)
Click Done

The app will automatically:

Create a Bridge device in your device list
Connect to your IntelliCenter
Discover all equipment and create child devices

Allow 10–15 seconds for all devices to appear after clicking Done.

Finding Your IntelliCenter IP
The easiest way is to check your router's device list and look for a device named IntelliCenter or Pentair. You can also find it in the official Pentair IntelliCenter mobile app under Settings → Status → Network.

Adjusting Set Points
The Pool Set Point and Spa Set Point devices support reading and changing the target temperature directly from Hubitat:

Open the set point device page
Use the setHeatingSetpoint command and enter the desired temperature in °F
The new set point is sent immediately to the controller
The device will update automatically when the controller confirms the change

Set point limits (40–104°F by default) can be adjusted in the set point device preferences.

Troubleshooting
No devices appearing after setup

Confirm the IP address is correct and reachable from your hub
Check that your hub and IntelliCenter are on the same subnet
Open the Bridge device page and check the connectionStatus attribute — it should show Connected
Check Hubitat logs for any error messages from the Bridge device

Connection status shows Disconnected

Open the Bridge device and click Initialize to force a reconnect
Verify the IntelliCenter is powered on and reachable
Confirm no firewall rules are blocking port 6680

A feature or circuit is missing

Enable Debug Logging in the Bridge device preferences
Click Initialize on the Bridge device and watch the logs
Look for the missing device's object name (e.g. FTR01, C0003) in the log output
If the object appears but is being skipped, note the OBJTYP and SUBTYP values and open a GitHub issue

Set point not updating when changed from another app

The integration subscribes to live push updates from the controller — set point changes made in the Pentair app or on the panel should reflect within a few seconds
If the value appears stuck, click Refresh on the Bridge device to request a full state update
If the set point child device was created before version 1.1.0, delete it manually and click Initialize on the Bridge — it will be recreated with the correct driver

Duplicate devices appeared

This can happen on first install if the app is initialized more than once
Manually delete any duplicate devices from the Devices page — they will not be recreated

Devices not updating

The integration uses live push updates from the controller — no polling needed
If values appear stuck, click Refresh on the Bridge device to request a full state update


Removing the Integration

Go to Devices and delete the IntelliCenter Bridge device and all child devices
Go to Apps and remove the Pentair IntelliCenter app instance
Go to Drivers Code and delete Pentair IntelliCenter Bridge
Go to Drivers Code and delete Pentair IntelliCenter Set Point
Go to Apps Code and delete Pentair IntelliCenter


Always delete devices before removing the app and driver code — Hubitat will not allow you to remove a driver that is still in use by a device.


Notes

The integration works entirely on your local network — no Pentair cloud account required
Password-protected IntelliCenter controllers are not currently supported
Compatible with Pentair IntelliCenter 1 (firmware 1.064+) and IntelliCenter 2 (firmware 3.006+)
Pump GPM sensor is only created when the pump reports a non-zero GPM value
Feature relays (e.g. blowers, motorized valves) are supported as of version 1.1.0
